cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.IR 

This paper is about weakly-supervised object detection (WSOD) using convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and objectness distillation. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel training mechanism for WSOD, which involves multiple regression targets and an adaptive linear combination of bottom-up and top-down objectness. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper evaluates its proposed method on benchmark datasets, which indicates that it may also belong to the category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
